1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:38,050 --> 00:00:42,970
[Blue Canvas of Youthful Days]

3
00:00:43,180 --> 00:00:46,180
[Episode 4: Love Is Controlling Yourself]

4
00:00:48,730 --> 00:00:50,590
Do you always have a stomachache?

5
00:01:13,220 --> 00:01:14,420
What kind of expression is that?

6
00:01:14,420 --> 00:01:15,670
Haven't you noticed that he's not feeling well?

7
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:18,200
Can you help him order some stomach medicine?

8
00:01:28,850 --> 00:01:30,720
All our classmates have joined the class chat group, right?

9
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,490
Add those who haven't joined the group to it.

10
00:01:32,490 --> 00:01:33,580
I don't hope to see

11
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,840
any classmates locked

12
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,810
in the Still Life Room after school again.

13
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:39,670
In the next two weeks, we'll enter the colour stage.

14
00:01:39,789 --> 00:01:41,890
To paint color, besides its similarity to sketching,

15
00:01:41,890 --> 00:01:44,890
you need to pay attention to the building of a sense of volume and texture.

16
00:01:44,890 --> 00:01:46,090
You should also pay extra attention to the methods

17
00:01:46,090 --> 00:01:47,850
and techniques of using pigments.

18
00:01:47,850 --> 00:01:51,060
Gouache and propylene can be used in most exams.

19
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,460
So, the studio is closed for holiday this afternoon.

20
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:55,660
Go and buy the materials you should buy.

21
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:57,130
Later, I'll ask the Class Adviser

22
00:01:57,130 --> 00:01:59,460
to send the list of the materials to the class chat group.

23
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:00,620
Do you all understand?

24
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,700
Yes.

25
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:02,790
Take your drawings.

26
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:03,920
Get ready for class.

27
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:13,650
[Smartphone Pouches]

28
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,590
Add me to the class chat group later.

29
00:02:09,590 --> 00:02:10,789
I entered this school later than you.

30
00:02:10,789 --> 00:02:12,060
There's a class chat group?

31
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:13,290
I'll add you to this group.

32
00:02:13,290 --> 00:02:14,390
I'm the group leader.

33
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:16,520
Where did you come from? You scared me.

34
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:17,310
Oh, by the way, Xiao,

35
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:18,950
I want to discuss something with you.

36
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:20,120
What are you up to this time?

37
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,360
No, yesterday, the girl in Class A

38
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,060
admitted defeat.

39
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,860
She's going to apologize to everyone face to face.

40
00:02:24,860 --> 00:02:26,980
I think as a young girl,

41
00:02:27,010 --> 00:02:28,350
she talked harshly,

42
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,140
but she...

43
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:30,420
wasn't

44
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:31,860
wrong.

45
00:02:32,690 --> 00:02:34,620
There's something wrong with you.

46
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:36,690
There's really something wrong with you.

47
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,510
I'm quite reasonable. Okay?

48
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:42,340
You can't maliciously speculate on me just because I'm reasonable.

49
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,630
Qin Xiao.

50
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:47,060
Qi Lu.

51
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:48,950
I admit defeat.

52
00:02:49,420 --> 00:02:51,010
I'm here to apologize.

53
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,000
Well, no need.

54
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:53,100
We are friends.

55
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:54,600
They won't blame you.

56
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:55,720
Don't take it to heart.

57
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:58,690
Don't attach much importance to comparison, either.

58
00:02:58,690 --> 00:02:59,960
Actually, you can draw well.

59
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,390
But out of this studio, there are many other people who can also draw well.

60
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:05,450
Don't compare yourself with others.

61
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:06,860
It's not something important.

62
00:03:06,860 --> 00:03:07,760
He means that

63
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:08,790
it's just a small misunderstanding.

64
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:09,960
Don't take it to heart.

65
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,660
Yes.

66
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,120
Thank you, Qin Xiao.

67
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,060
Although I have no intention to compare myself with others,

68
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,460
I still want to thank you.

69
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,820
Stop looking.

70
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:25,920
That's so sweet.

71
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,190
But she's really so cute.

72
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:08,990
[Super Craftsman Painting Materials]

73
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,910
It's 168.4 yuan in total.

74
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:25,100
WeChat or Alipay?

75
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:29,580
Aren't the pigments on that shelf sold with a 40% discount?

76
00:04:29,590 --> 00:04:30,840
Well, the rule is that for the 36 colors,

77
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:31,890
if you buy enough basic quantities,

78
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:34,490
there will a 40% discount for all the pigments.

79
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,500
Alright. I'll take a look again.

80
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,540
I'll put it here first.

81
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:01,790
Wu.

82
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:02,530
Oh.

83
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:04,470
What a rare guest.

84
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,410
Xiao,

85
00:05:05,770 --> 00:05:07,430
don't you have classes every day?

86
00:05:07,430 --> 00:05:09,420
How come you have time to visit here today?

87
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:10,060
Wu.

88
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,820
Last time, didn't you say on the phone that

89
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:13,590
you wanted me to help you draw something for your business?

90
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:14,290
I'm here to take a look.

91
00:05:14,290 --> 00:05:15,360
I want to do a part-time job.

92
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,310
Come on.

93
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:17,620
I was going to see you next week.

94
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:18,330
Come up.

95
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,850
Have you noticed this wall?

96
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,500
I want you to draw something on this wall.

97
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,290
You can draw graffiti or anything else.

98
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:30,260
Just draw whatever you want.

99
00:05:30,260 --> 00:05:32,190
I also don't know how to explain it.

100
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,330
I'll offer all the pigments to you.

101
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:37,320
I'll also give you 5,000 yuan separately.

102
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,140
Well,

103
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,780
while you're drawing here,

104
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,580
keep an eye on the outside.

105
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:43,460
I'm going to do some small business inside.

106
00:05:43,460 --> 00:05:44,900
I'm worried that I might disturb the neighbors.

107
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,560
You've been living here for so many years.

108
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,560
You know the neighbors here so well.

109
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,420
People are going back and forth outside.

110
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:52,380
If there are any strangers,

111
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,700
tell our men inside about it.

112
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,350
Okay?

113
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,860
No problem, Wu.

114
00:05:57,890 --> 00:05:58,670
When?

115
00:06:00,580 --> 00:06:01,480
Next Tuesday.

116
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:04,530
Okay, Wu.

117
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:07,640
By that time, I'll ask for leave in advance if I can.

118
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,560
Have you bought all the painting materials on the list?

119
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:35,480
Do you want to draw sketches with me this afternoon?

120
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:38,200
[Supermarket]

121
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:42,820
Thank you.

122
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,120
Have some peanut kernels.

123
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,580
They're quite delicious.

124
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,700
I knew that you didn't come out to draw sketches.

125
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:56,340
We have to get full before we start drawing.

126
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:05,250
By the way,

127
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,500
where should I buy the pigments?

128
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:10,560
I don't know. My dad asked his secretary to buy them for me.

129
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,920
[Fried Food]

130
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:12,970
Should I prepare one more portion for you?

131
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:14,900
[Fried Food]

132
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:15,690
No need. I'll figure out a solution myself.

133
00:07:26,170 --> 00:07:27,750
You have to draw the shpae first.

134
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:28,750
The outside part.

135
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:48,710
You're indeed the winner of the Youth Award.

136
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,880
You've really made a difference after giving some advice.

137
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,580
Here you are. Eat it.

138
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,190
Eat it.

139
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:55,950
Let me take a bite.

140
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:04,850
Why are you so discouraged?

141
00:08:04,850 --> 00:08:05,380
Let's go.

142
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:08,310
Let me help you speed up.

143
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:09,060
No.

144
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:10,460
This road is quite steep.

145
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,270
I can ride.

146
00:08:14,310 --> 00:08:15,190
Okay.

147
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:19,300
How about I recommend a painting materials shop to you?

148
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:21,850
No need. I'll figure out a solution myself.

149
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:49,590
Brother, where are you?

150
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:52,000
Can I go see you?

151
00:09:09,570 --> 00:09:10,500
Are you happy?

152
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:13,090
I was worried that since it was so high,

153
00:09:13,090 --> 00:09:14,220
you would be scared.

154
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:17,100
I like to stay in high places.

155
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:20,950
The building I used to live in was much higher than Qin Xiao's house.

156
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,900
Was it the house of your parents?

157
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:25,500
It was not here.

158
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:30,520
You haven't contacted your parents for such a long time.

159
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,630
Is it really okay?

160
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:34,870
I ran out.

161
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,120
You ran out?

162
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:39,190
You ran away from home?

163
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:42,070
After they sent me to school,

164
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:43,930
we would be locked up

165
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:45,420
and get beaten up,

166
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,110
so I ran out.

167
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,970
That was a school?

168
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:52,330
It was also considered

169
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:53,840
as a hospital.

170
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,210
They saw my chatting records

171
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:05,410
and found out that I liked boys.

172
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,730
They said they would send me there

173
00:10:07,830 --> 00:10:09,500
and turn me into...

174
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:15,070
You've disappointed me so much.

175
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:18,230
Why did you do this kind of thing outside?

176
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,940
Don't come home.

177
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,400
I'll pretend that you're not my son.

178
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,510
You've really disappointed me so much.

179
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:26,780
Why did you do this kind of thing outside?

180
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,390
Don't come home.

181
00:10:28,390 --> 00:10:30,690
I'll pretend that you're not my son.

182
00:10:30,690 --> 00:10:31,640
Get lost!

183
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:32,930
Tan.

184
00:10:33,650 --> 00:10:35,920
After Qin Xiao helps his grandpa settle down,

185
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:37,380
do you want to go to school?

186
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,170
Do I have to go to school?

187
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,340
It's also okay if you don't go to school.

188
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:44,250
You can do something you like.

189
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:45,380
Well,

190
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,910
can I learn how to make delicious food?

191
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,720
You want to learn how to cook?

192
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:51,090
It's very difficult.

193
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:52,360
You've underestimated me.

194
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,070
I was once an apprentice in the kitchen of a restaurant.

195
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:54,830
Okay.

196
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:56,690
When this year's exam is over,

197
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:58,010
I'll take you to sign up for a class.

198
00:10:58,010 --> 00:10:59,390
I'll also take the class myself

199
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,050
to improve my cooking skills.

200
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:13,880
Hello.

201
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,710
Can you take a photo for us?

202
00:11:15,710 --> 00:11:16,260
Sure.

203
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,060
Thank you.

204
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:19,950
Take two steps back.

205
00:11:21,710 --> 00:11:22,770
Look at the camera.

206
00:11:22,770 --> 00:11:23,250
Three.

207
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:23,860
Two.

208
00:11:23,890 --> 00:11:24,660
One.

209
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:35,540
Where are you?

210
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:43,090
Well,

211
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,250
you are that lazy?

212
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,520
When you went home from school,

213
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,320
couldn't you take it from my shop on your way home?

214
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,850
Why did you have to ask for the takeout service?

215
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:50,600
Liu asked us to prepare some pigments, didn't he?

216
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,420
So I went home

217
00:11:51,450 --> 00:11:52,850
and moved my things here.

218
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,120
This isn't your home?

219
00:11:55,490 --> 00:11:57,720
There's cola in the fridge. Do you want to drink it?

220
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,320
Forget it.

221
00:11:58,620 --> 00:11:59,560
Then I have to go back now.

222
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,210
Wait.

223
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,620
Carry these things away.

224
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,620
Don't reject me in such a hurry first.

225
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:15,310
I used these gouaches and paint brushes before.

226
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,620
Some of them are not too wet now.

227
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:18,890
Some of them got a bit dirty when I blended the colors previously,

228
00:12:18,890 --> 00:12:20,200
so I don't want to use them anymore.

229
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,730
They've also got dry by the heater in my house.

230
00:12:23,060 --> 00:12:24,060
I'm thinking that

231
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,810
if you need any of them,

232
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,520
just take them away directly.

233
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:30,690
You were also in the painting materials shop

234
00:12:30,690 --> 00:12:31,620
this afternoon?

235
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,020
You don't need to feel embarrassed.

236
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,660
The cost of the color lessons

237
00:12:38,990 --> 00:12:40,590
is a little big for me indeed.

238
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:41,080
Thanks.

239
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,160
If you feel embarrassed,

240
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,390
you can do me a favor.

241
00:12:46,810 --> 00:12:48,870
You have an ill intention, don't you?

242
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:50,870
I'm colour-blind.

243
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:52,070
I can't blend colors.

244
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:53,950
Help me blend the colors, Xiao.

245
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:54,870
How about this?

246
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:56,920
You'll be fully in charge of tidying up my pigment boxes,

247
00:12:56,920 --> 00:13:01,120
and I'll pay all the cost for your color tool kits in the training camp. Okay?

248
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:05,870
Where are your things?

249
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:07,400
Teach me how to tidy them up.

250
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:12,120
To paint propylene or gouache,

251
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,880
I usually like using this kind of tool.

252
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:15,960
I'm used to lining up the paint boxes like this.

253
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,280
After filling a grid, wipe it with sponge.

254
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,670
Then fill another grid.

255
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:22,740
After finish handling all the things, spray some water to keep them moist.

256
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:26,600
Too much water isn't okay. Otherwise, The gouache will get degummed.

257
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:44,110
It looks like it's not easy to surpass you in paiting color.

258
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:46,310
It's not that hard.

259
00:13:46,590 --> 00:13:50,540
When I was a kid, I learned drawing with the students who prepared for the college entrance exam.

260
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:51,960
Every time I went to the training camp,

261
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:55,620
there were some people who could draw better than me after starting from scratch.

262
00:13:55,620 --> 00:13:58,110
But there were only these several people who could do so, right?

263
00:13:58,110 --> 00:13:59,760
That was because there were so many students

264
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,020
in this one art studio,

265
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:03,900
and only a few of them were really suitable for painting.

266
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:05,670
At least, among these several people in Boyi,

267
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:07,670
Mr. Qi Lu is also included, isn't he?

268
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:09,980
The scale of Liu's studio is too small.

269
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,890
Have you seen any small studio that can help

270
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:13,930
several students get admitted to Huajing in a year?

271
00:14:13,930 --> 00:14:15,590
You still need to have a dream.

272
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:16,860
What if it comes true?

273
00:14:21,370 --> 00:14:23,570
You will definitely get admitted to it.

274
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:24,890
What?

275
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:27,680
Are you also good at fortune-telling, Mr. Qi?

276
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,500
I started drawing when I was four.

